      • getSpecificAnnotationPreferences

        public SpecificAnnotationSettings getSpecificAnnotationPreferences(String spectrumKey,
                                                                   SpectrumIdentificationAssumption spectrumIdentificationAssumption,
                                                                   SequenceMatchingPreferences sequenceMatchingPreferences,
                                                                   SequenceMatchingPreferences ptmSequenceMatchingPreferences)
                                                            throws IOException,
                                                                   InterruptedException,
                                                                   ClassNotFoundException,
                                                                   SQLException
        Returns the annotation preferences specific to a spectrum and an identification assumption.
        Parameters:
        spectrumKey - the key of the spectrum to annotate
        spectrumIdentificationAssumption - the spectrum identification assumption to annotate with
        sequenceMatchingPreferences - the sequence matching preferences for peptide to protein mapping
        ptmSequenceMatchingPreferences - the sequence matching preferences for PTM to peptide mapping
        Returns:
        the annotation preferences specific to a spectrum and an identification assumption
        Throws:
        IOException - exception thrown whenever an error occurred while interacting with a file while mapping potential modification sites
        InterruptedException - exception thrown whenever a threading issue occurred while mapping potential modification sites
        ClassNotFoundException - exception thrown whenever an error occurred while deserializing an object from the ProteinTree
        SQLException - exception thrown whenever an error occurred while interacting with the ProteinTree
